Organizers of the yearly Africa International Film Festival, AFRIFF, have announced  dates and partners for 2019 edition.<img class="size-full wp-image-1250392 aligncenter" src="https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/download-3.jpg?resize=640%2C703&#038;ssl=1" alt="AFRIFF, Xenophobic" width="640" height="703" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/download-3.jpg?w=1500&amp;ssl=1 1500w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/download-3.jpg?resize=273%2C300&amp;ssl=1 273w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/download-3.jpg?resize=768%2C843&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/download-3.jpg?resize=933%2C1024&amp;ssl=1 933w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/download-3.jpg?resize=53%2C58&amp;ssl=1 53w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/download-3.jpg?resize=177%2C194&amp;ssl=1 177w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/download-3.jpg?resize=118%2C130&amp;ssl=1 118w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/download-3.jpg?resize=560%2C615&amp;ssl=1 560w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/download-3.jpg?w=1280&amp;ssl=1 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> The festival is expected to kick off  on Sunday,  November 10, through Saturday, November 16, 2019, at the newly constructed FfilmHouse Cinemas at Landmark Retail Village, Victoria Island. Speaking at a press parley, in Lagos, Chioma Ude, AFRIFF founder and Executive Director said, “International film matters more than ever. Our varied programme of the very best of cinema has the power of allowing us to understand how people with very different circumstances from all over the globe live, work and play. Continuing, she added: “We are proud to theme this year’s festival as one dedicated to SHEROES, those who enable us to dream and to celebrate story telling which challenge society. We are very much focused on training and supporting more female filmmakers this year and beyond.” Ethiopia’s Oromo people prepare to mark Irreecha festival(Opens in a new browser tab) Chioma Ude was also joined by Festival sponsors, Access Bank, US Consulate, Nvivo TV, National Film Video Censors Board, Filmhouse Group and Century Group.” Vanguard  The organisers of the annual Africa International Film Festival (AFRIFF) have unveiled an impressive line-up of festival programme which holds in Lagos, from November 8 through 15, 2015. October 10, 2015 In "Home Video People" THE African International Film Festival – AFRIFF 2015 might have come and gone, but one memory of the week long event that caught the attention of many was the participation of foremost Nigerian automobile brand Peugeot in the festival. The company came not as real participant in the workshops or… December 3, 2015 In "News" Organizers of the 16th edition of Abuja International Film Festival, AIFF, and The Africa International Film Festival, AFRIFF, have announced the immediate suspension of all South African films submitted for the festival scheduled to hold from 22nd through 25th of October 2019, following the fresh attacks on Nigerians and other… September 7, 2019 In "Entertainment"